DENGUE - COLOMBIA (05): 1980-1997
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Dengue - Colombia 970722135923
Dengue - Colombia (02) 970722155113
Dengue - Colombia: under-/mis-reporting 970329161801
Dengue - Colombia (03) 971103012153
Dengue/DHF - Colombia 950830, 950903
Date: Mon, 03 Nov 1997 19:03:09 -0800
From: Dr. Steve Berger <<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: Data extracted from GIDEON software

Dengue: Potential exists for transmission along the Atlantic coast,
Magdalena River Valley, Cauca River Valley, Putumayo Intendancy and
Cordillera Oriental slopes. Dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) was first
reported in 1985. No cases were reported during 1960 to 1970.
Cases reported since 1980 are as follows:
Year Number of Cases Reported
1980 9,894
1981 10,790
1982 6,776
1983 12,919
1984 7,540
1985 82,272 (including 1 DHF, fatal)
1986 7,881
1987 17,510
1988 16,308
1989 10,092 (1 DHF)
1990 17,389 (including 39 of DHF & one fatality)
1991 15,103 (including 39 of DHF & one fatality)
1992 59,357 (496 DHF, 4 fatal)
1993 8,449
1994 774
1995 18,398 (107 DHF, 10 fatal)
1996 7,787 (12 fatal)
83% of elementary school children in Cali were seropositive in 1997.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
